---
import RootLayout from "@/layouts/RootLayout.astro";
import "@/styles/global.scss";
import Binding from "@/zines/Binding.astro";
import Module1 from "@/zines/Module1.astro";
import Module2 from "@/zines/Module2.astro";
---

<RootLayout>
  <main>
    <h1>The Death of Print Media</h1>
    <p>ARCH 346: Anthropology of Design<br />By Evan Kirkiles</p>
    <div class="intro">
      <div class="contents">
        <p>
          My final project for ARCH 346 is a design response exploring the
          concept of the death of print media. The main body of the project is
          less the content in the zines than the CSS layout framework seen on
          this page that allows printing zine impositions directly from the
          browser. The goal is to straddle the line between digital and print
          publishing, creating a unified format that can exist both on the web
          and in printable book form without additional labor.
        </p>
        <p
          >Since the inception of digital publishing, print publishing has been
          in decline. This project investigates a technical manner by which
          print and digital might be merged in a democratic, distributable
          manner. Naturally, I do not expect to match the massive featureset of
          an enterprise tool like InDesignâ€”rather, I envision this project as a
          zine publishing framework. Zines have historically been produced by
          communities with minimal resources and a DIY attitude, for which the
          portability of a website-based typesetting program would be quite
          useful.</p
        >
        <hr />
        <h2 class="instruct">Instructions</h2>
        <p
          >For best print output results, please use either Chrome or Firefox.
          Enable backgrounds, but disable headers and footers. Pick any page
          size or orientation you wish and the framework will attempt to morph
          its content to match. Sample outputs can be found on the right.</p
        >
        <p>To fold and assemble the zines, follow the below guide:</p>
        <img src="/img/binding/zineMaker.jpeg" class="guide both-print" />
      </div>
      <div class="actions no-print">
        <button id="print">Print</button>
        <a href="https://github.com/evankirkiles/arch-zine">View the Code</a>
        <a href="/files/A4Portrait.pdf">Sample: A4, Portrait</a>
        <a href="/files/A3Landscape.pdf">Sample: A3, Landscape</a>
        <a href="/files/LetterLandscape.pdf">Sample: Letter, Landscape</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>
  <h2 class="no-print">[0] Introduction</h2>
  <Binding />
  <h2 class="no-print">[1] An Abridged History of Printing</h2>
  <Module1 />
  <h2 class="no-print">[2] Print Media Is Dying</h2>
  <Module2 />
</RootLayout>

<script>
  const printButton = document.querySelector<HTMLButtonElement>("#print");
  printButton?.addEventListener("click", () => window.print());
</script>

<style lang="scss">
  .intro {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-block-start: 1rem;
  }

  .instruct {
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .contents {
    flex: 100;
    min-inline-size: min(100%, 500px);
  }

  hr {
    margin-block: 1rem;
  }

  .guide {
    inline-size: 100%;
    block-size: auto;
  }

  .actions {
    display: flex;
    flex: 1;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    min-inline-size: 28ch;

    & > * {
      display: block;
      border: 1px solid currentColor;
      padding: 0.5rem 2rem;
      inline-size: 100%;
      color: black;
      text-align: center;
      text-decoration: none;

      &:hover {
        background-color: black;
        color: white;
      }
    }

    @media print {
      display: none;
    }
  }

  #print {
    background-color: #0000ff;
    color: white;

    &:hover {
      background-color: black;
    }
  }
</style>
